🧾 SOP: Azure Warranty Portal Project (End-to-End)
🧱 PHASE 1 — Create GitHub Repository
Step 1: Create repo
Go to GitHub
Create repository:
warranty-portal
Public (for lab)
Initialize with README (optional)
Step 2: Clone to WSL
cd ~
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/warranty-portal.git
cd warranty-portal
Step 3: Configure Git identity (first time only)
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your-email"
🌐 PHASE 2 — Create Azure App Service
Step 4: Create App Service

Azure Portal → App Service → Create

OS: Linux
Runtime: PHP 8.3
Plan: B1
Region: same as DB
Step 5: Enable GitHub Deployment

App Service → Deployment Center:

Source: GitHub
Repo: warranty-portal
Branch: main

✔ This creates CI/CD pipeline automatically

🧾 PHASE 3 — Build Application (PHP)
Step 6: Create index.php
Form fields:
- name
- email
- address
- issue
- description

Basic structure:

<form method="POST">
Step 7: Add DB connection (PDO)
$server = "your-server.database.windows.net";
$database = "your-db";
$username = "your-user";
$password = "your-password";
Step 8: Insert logic
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    $stmt = $conn->prepare("INSERT INTO WarrantyRequests (...) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)");
    $stmt->execute([...]);
}
Step 9: Commit and push initial code
git add .
git commit -m "Initial warranty portal app"
git push origin main
🗄️ PHASE 4 — Create Azure SQL Database
Step 10: Create SQL DB

Azure Portal:

Database: warrantyportaldatabase
Server: new SQL server
Step 11: Configure firewall

Enable:

Allow Azure services: YES
Add client IP: YES
Step 12: Create table

Run in Query Editor:

CREATE TABLE WarrantyRequests (
    Id INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
    CustomerName NVARCHAR(100),
    Email NVARCHAR(100),
    Address NVARCHAR(200),
    IssueType NVARCHAR(50),
    Description NVARCHAR(MAX),
    CreatedAt DATETIME DEFAULT GETDATE()
);
🔗 PHASE 5 — Connect App → SQL
Step 13: Update connection string

Ensure:

server = Azure SQL server
database = correct DB name
username = SQL user
password = SQL password
Step 14: Test DB insert manually (optional)
INSERT INTO WarrantyRequests (...)
VALUES (...)
Step 15: Commit DB integration
git add .
git commit -m "Add SQL integration"
git push origin main
🚀 PHASE 6 — CI/CD Deployment Flow
Step 16: Any change workflow

Every update follows:

git add .
git commit -m "update message"
git push origin main
Step 17: Deployment pipeline

After push:

GitHub → Actions → Build → Deploy → Azure App Service
🧪 PHASE 7 — Testing
Step 18: Verify app

Open:

https://<your-app>.azurewebsites.net
Step 19: Submit form test
Fill form
Submit
Check DB:
SELECT * FROM WarrantyRequests;
🧠 PHASE 8 — Debug SOP
If app shows 404:
Check form action URL
Check deployment logs
If DB error:
Check table exists
Check connection string
If CI/CD not working:
Check GitHub Actions
Check Deployment Center
🔁 PHASE 9 — Daily Workflow (IMPORTANT)
Your normal development cycle:
1. Edit index.php in WSL
2. git add .
3. git commit -m "change"
4. git push origin main
5. Azure auto deploys
🏁 FINAL ARCHITECTURE
Developer (WSL)
   ↓
GitHub Repo
   ↓
GitHub Actions (CI/CD)
   ↓
Azure App Service (PHP)
   ↓
Azure SQL Database
